reviews.text: The food was delicious. We had great service. The loaded fries were really good! The pan pizza is really soft and has a nice texture. The cheesy isn't too greasy like other places. The pizza sauce is the right balance. I was thrilled that it wasn't overly sweet like many other places in central Indiana. The bathrooms are super small, but there is a baby changing station in the women's room. We'll definitely be returning in the future.

Food tastes great, always does. Service was lacking a bit, empty drinks and lettuce on salad bar  while more people working than dinning amd this was a thin crust pizza. Topoing order accuracy was lost in transit also. No offer to correct any issues....staff is young so we just let it go but some improvements would be nice to before revisting as we will be at some point because that PIZZA IS GOOD & SALAD BARS ARE SWELL!

We ordered a pepperoni pizza with basil, and it was absolutely amazing‚Äîthe crust was perfectly baked and full of flavor, the kind of crust you actually want to eat every last bite of. We also tried the cheese bread, which was delicious on its own, but the sauces really took it to the next level. The cheese sauce was solid, but the garlic sauce completely stole the show‚Äîit was rich, garlicky, and the perfect dip.

On top of the great food, the staff were incredibly friendly and welcoming, which made the whole visit even better. The restaurant itself was adorable‚Äîcozy, inviting, and just a fun place to sit and enjoy a meal.

Overall, everything from the food to the atmosphere to the service was spot on. Definitely a place I‚Äôd recommend and can‚Äôt wait to come back to!

We ordered breadsticks and pretzels for the appetizer and  pizza, alfredo and spaghetti for lunch. It was amazing! The breadsticks are 10 out of 10! Deluxe pizza, chefs kiss! Go there, it's a great place in a great setting. Our waitress was so nice and very good at her job!

While nannying this summer we stopped at this Pizzeria one day for lunch. We ordered carryout for a small cheese pizza and a cookie, and they did not disappoint! The pizza was delicious, however I felt the cookie pie was a little grainy but it was still nice and gooey. The hostess was wonderful and the wait was only 10 minutes, incredibly fast for fresh baked items. I will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.text: Nothing special AT ALL about this pizza. Maybe I was expecting more so I‚Äôll take some blameü§® Just a generic taste, nothing unique at all. You can get the same taste from a regular frozen pizza‚Ä¶.and it won‚Äôt cost as much!

detailedReviews.author: Trent Fairbrother
detailedReviews.text:
I have never had a truly religious experience while eating food until dining at Zionsville Pizzeria. From the genuine and sincere smiles of the staff to the what I can only describe as divine pizza. There breadsticks brought a single tear to my eye reminding me of breadsticks I had as a child.

To say this dining experience is immaculate is an understatement. I cannot recommend this restaurant enough. I am excited for my next of many ventures to this absolute gem hidden in Zionsville.

detailedReviews.text:
The waitress was pretty awesome! My biggest complaint was that we came for the buffet, and it was empty pretty much the whole time........ We literally left hungry. The pizza we did have was amazing I loved the crust and toppings and the quantity and quality of them.
I dinged the service only because of the lack of items offered on the buffet. I also dinged the atmosphere because you couldn't hear anything the person next to you said because of how loud the room was.

P.S. the parking is also a nightmare, but that's not the restaurant's fault. Parking in Zionsville is horrible everywhere.

detailedReviews.author: Mark Sevenich
detailedReviews.text:
So glad we stopped in.  Dishes are made on-site, fresh.  Food had excellent flavor.  Sauce had the right mix of seasoning and real chunks of tomatoes paired with the meatballs.  Meatballs were all beef, no fillers.  Cheesy bread was excellent.  Cooked the way your grandmother would cook... from scratch.

The cheese melted over the meatballs and for the cheesy bread is a mouth watering blend of 3 cheeses that is utterly smooth.  The sauce was perfect.  Not hot, not sweet, yet rather a balance of italian flavor and appropriate spices.  No one spice was overpowering.  The flavor danced.

detailedReviews.author: Janeesh Sekkath Veedu
detailedReviews.text: I don‚Äôt post a lot of negative reviews for local businesses but I think it is necessary for improvement. Service was delayed for about 10 minutes after we got checked in. Our waitress apologized for the delay and took our orders. Drinks were in quick but we had to wait forever for breadsticks! Probably around 30 minutes. Fortunately our kids weren‚Äôt super hungry else we would have walked out. And then the pizza took another 30-40 minutes. They weren‚Äôt busy and we understand that orders can be delayed at any restaurant but this was beyond a reasonable wait time. Also we didn‚Äôt know there was a 4$ surcharge for adding Alfredo sauce to a 8$ kids pasta. 50% surcharge. Should have been specified in the menu. Would have still paid for it but good to know in advance. We intentionally choose local restaurants for our meals but experiences like this make us question our choices.

detailedReviews.author: Jason Harrell
detailedReviews.text: Cozy place for lunch, nice salad bar! Scenery a plus

detailedReviews.author: Becky Baskerville

detailedReviews.author: Diane Slama
detailedReviews.text: We ordered a delicious sausage pizza and their artichoke and spinach bread special. It was also delicious.  We highly recommend zionsville pizzeria.

detailedReviews.author: Mark Fraizer
detailedReviews.text: Wow, what a horrible experience!  We ordered two pizza‚Äôs,two breadstick orders and two cheese stick orders which came to $77, ok for a locally owned pizza restaurant.  I don‚Äôt mind paying for what should be premium food.  We ordered at 5:40 and told it would be about an hour and the address is less than three miles from the restaurant, no problem an hour is expected on a Sunday evening.  After several calls the order showed up at 7:50 well over two hours later. The food was not only cold, but stale.  Sad sad sad, don‚Äôt really understand how these folks stay in business.  We bypassed the chain restaurants to spend and keep our money local, big mistake.  It was horrible and I would not recommend this restaurant to anyone.   IF could rate them a zero I would.  If you do decide to order from these folks, I would go and pick your order up.  What a waste of $77 not including the tip.  Really made me upset when they told us the order would be there in 5 minutes and it was 40 minutes later when it showed up. Sad, sad ,sad!

From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm smiles and genuine hospitality. The staff went above and beyond to ensure that my dining experience was nothing short of perfect.

detailedReviews.text: Used to be our favorite but after tonight we will not return.  We placed our online delivery order at 5:53 pm on a Wednesday. detailedReviews.text: It was our favorite pizzeria until today, the service was terrible, they served us water in disposable cups because the other were dirty (said by the waitress). I ordered a pizza with procciuto and as you see in the photo, those red dots are the ‚Äúbits‚Äù of procciuto. But the most incredible thing is that they served us glasses of water and charged for them!! Not even bottled water, sink water with ice and they charged for it. This is incredible!

detailedReviews.author: Mary Taber
detailedReviews.text:
Seriously the best pizza in town! There are so many pizza joints but this one is the best tasting for sure! Locally/family owned business and I enjoy supporting local. The owner always tries to get to know you a bit more each time you come in. Very friendly service.
There are so many topping choices, which is awesome and I like that so much! Love the variety. Peppadew peppers are my fave, paired with pepperoni. Always plenty of cheese which I thoroughly enjoy! I feel like chain pizza places are so skimpy these days and always have to ask for extra and pay more in order to get what is deemed as ‚Äúnormal‚Äù.

Overall, love this place! I go here probably twice a month or more.

detailedReviews.author: Blaine Milburn
detailedReviews.text: Zionsville Pizzaria is hands down one of the best pizza locations I‚Äôve had in the United States. Their crust is something special. Their ultimate cheese pizza is legendary. When I ask my friends and family if they want Zionsville Pizza, a light goes off in each of their eyes. It‚Äôs that good.

detailedReviews.author: Cheryl Crowder
detailedReviews.text: We heard great reviews about this pizza, and they were right! We had mozzarella sticks, chicken and sausage pizza, and BBQ chicken pizza. It was even better than expected! The service was quick and nice. We will be going again when we are in the area!

detailedReviews.author: Rita Southern
detailedReviews.text: Very good pizza! Great service!

detailedReviews.author: Debra Crawford
detailedReviews.text: Tried for the first time and had delivered New Years Day.  We love thin, crispy crust so we‚Äôre a little disappointed UNTIL we placed on a hot pizza stone and baked until crispy‚Ä¶absolutely the best pizza!  Quality ingredients, delicious sauce, great crust everything you want in a good pizza.  I would only suggest baking longer..other than that Excellent!  Definitely will be our pizza place.  We ordered the pepperoni/sausage peppidew and a vegetarian pizza.

The food and service were great.

detailedReviews.author: paul nicholas
detailedReviews.text:
The pizza is especially good.

They have a coupon system, but it is horrible.  You have to subscribe to it, and it sends you a text message with a weird web link that takes you to a weird website with a .app domain. Then it gives you a coupon code that expires in an hour. And the discounts aren't even that good. Like if you buy a pizza, you get a 12" cheese for half price. But you can't use it to online order. So you have to call in your order, then keep that link open in your browser to show them your phone in person when you pick up your pizza.  I just decreased the rating by 2 stars because it is almost like they are trying to discourage you from using it. Or you could pay full price.

detailedReviews.author: Susan Graham
detailedReviews.text: I stopped in for a late lunch today. The lunch buffet was awesome!  The salad bar was very fresh & full of  tasty veggies. It complemented the pizza very well!  I'll be back for sure. Can't wait to try the cannolis for dessert!

The Pepperoni Pizza: absolutely worth it. My kids are picky and they even proclaimed to be the best pizza they‚Äôve had. The breadsticks alone were worth the purchase. Extremely soft and flavorful. We will be returning next year when tournament time rolls around.
